liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Matildas played England in April in their last friendly before the whole squad came back to Australia for World Cup preparations. There was no Steph Catley (or Caitlin Foord) in the side that day and that meant Charlotte Grant was in the starting line-up at the back. After Sam Kerr slotted in the first half, 21-year-old Grant scored her first international goal to help end the Lionesses' 30-match unbeaten run. Grant hasn't had a run in this World Cup yet, with the Carpenter-Kennedy-Clare-Catley backline locked into place, but will she come on as some sort of anti-England specialist?
